To complete the proof of the Chinese Remainder Theorem (CRT) in the given Lean 4 context, we need to fill in the missing parts of the proof for the `chineseMap` function and its associated properties.

The main goal at the end of the `chineseMap` definition is to prove that the kernel of the map `(fun i => Quotient.mk (I i))` is contained in the intersection of the ideals `I i`. This is a standard condition required for the CRT to hold, ensuring that the map is well-defined on the quotient ring.

