To complete the proof of the Chinese Remainder Theorem (CRT) for ideals in a commutative ring, we need to show that the map `chineseMap` is well-defined. This involves proving that the kernel of the map `Pi.ringHom fun i => Quotient.mk (I i)` is contained within the intersection of the ideals `I i`.

